title: Russia, Ukraine trade POWs with no new word of passengers on downed plane
description: Moscow claimed 65 Ukrainian POWs were killed in the destruction of a Russian military jet last week. Ukraine insists Russia has provided no such evidence.

title: With Hungary blocking Ukraine aid, E.U. desperate for workarounds
description: Hungary’s veto of Ukraine aid has forced the European Union to consider workarounds in the short term and is bolstering calls to change rules on unanimous voting.

title: Zelensky to oust Ukraine’s top general amid tension over new mobilization
description: Ukraine’s president told Gen. Valery Zaluzhny, the top commander since Russia’s February 2022 invasion, that he was being dismissed. A formal order is expected this week.

title: Australian TV network edits female lawmaker’s photo to be more revealing
description: State lawmaker Georgie Purcell said she “can’t imagine this happening to a male” colleague. The Nine Network apologized, citing an AI tool error.

title: For second time in 24 hours, ex-Pakistani leader Khan sentenced to prison
description: Khan was sentenced to 14 years in prison in a corruption case just days before Pakistan’s general election, following a 10-year sentence the day before.

title: African production of natural gas poses a vexing climate challenge
description: Senegalese President Macky Sall has said denying the country the chance to tap its reserves is “climate fanaticism.”

title: Middle East conflict live updates: Biden blames Iran for supplying weapons that killed 3 U.S. troops in Jordan
description: The president said he had decided on how to respond to the attack but did not offer details. “I don’t think we need a wider war in the Middle East,” he said.

title: Egypt-Israel ties in jeopardy over intensifying Gaza border dispute
description: The prospect of Israeli troops returning to the Gaza-Egypt border has set off alarm bells in Cairo, with officials saying it would undermine the 1979 peace treaty.

title: Behind Biden’s Middle East crises is the long tail of Trump’s legacy
description: Donald Trump and Republican colleagues are pinning the sense of chaos in the Middle East on the Biden administration. But Trump set in motion the deepening risk of a nuclear Iran and encouraged the acceleration of Israel’s far-right drift.

title: Details bedevil Gaza hostages-for-prisoners ‘framework’ deal
description: Negotiators are working on a six-week pause in Israel-Hamas fighting, which would see the release of all remaining civilian captives in exchange for Palestinian prisoners.

title: Israeli intelligence prompted U.S. to quickly cut Gaza aid funding
description: The U.N. relief agency must conduct a “credible investigation” of workers alleged to have participated in the Oct. 7 attacks, a senior U.S. official said.
